Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Dice @Sweet Potato{1} into 1⁄2-inch pieces.

Toss sweet potato on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until lightly browned and tender, ~{18-20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, heat a large dry pan over medium-high heat. Add @sunflower seeds{1/2%ounce} and toast, stirring frequently, until fragrant and just beginning to brown, ~{2-3%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #small bowl{}. Wipe out pan.

Quarter @lemon{1}. Halve and core @apple{1}; thinly slice into half-moons.

== Dressing ==

In a large bowl, whisk together @Dijon mustard{2%teaspoon}, @sugar{1/2%teaspoon}, a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon}, juice from half the lemon, salt, and pepper until combined.

> Use 1 tsp sugar for 4 servings.

== Salad ==

Add apple and @kale, broccoli, and Brussels sprouts mix{8%ounce} to bowl with dressing; toss to combine. Set aside to marinate, tossing occasionally.

Open package of @chicken breast{10%ounce}(chopped) and drain off any excess liquid. Season all over with @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, salt, and pepper. Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for sunflower seeds over medium-high heat. Add chicken; cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Add roasted sweet potato, sunflower seeds, and half the chicken to bowl with salad; toss to combine. Taste and add more olive oil and lemon juice or season with more salt and pepper if desired.

Divide salad between bowls; top with remaining chicken and serve with any remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.